### 3. IMPACT ANALYSIS: THE VALUE CHAIN

#### Phase 1: Pre-Design & Strategy (High Disruption / High Value)
*   **Generative Feasibility:** Text-to-3D (e.g., Luma AI, Meshy, Midjourney + ControlNet) + GIS data allows **100+ massing options in hours**, not weeks. Enables "Optioneering" as a billable service.
*   **Predictive Analytics:** LLMs (GPT-4/Claude) ingest zoning codes, climate data, and market comps to produce **instant "Highest & Best Use" reports**.
*   **Strategic Shift:** *Move from selling "Design" to selling "Decision Confidence."*

#### Phase 2: Schematic & Design Development (Core Disruption)
*   **Text-to-BIM / Image-to-BIM:** Tools (Hypar, TestFit, Finch3D, Arko.ai, Veras) convert prompts/sketches → Revit/Rhino geometry + Data.
*   **Performance-Driven Design:** Real-time Energy/Daylight/Carbon feedback loops (Cove.tool, Sefaira, Ladybug) embedded *inside* the modeling environment.
*   **Code Compliance Automation:** AI agents checking egress, accessibility, fire ratings against IBC/local amendments *continuously*.
*   **Risk:** **"Black Box" Liability.** If AI generates a non-compliant stair, who is the "Author"? Current contracts (AIA B101) are silent.

#### Phase 3: Construction Documentation (High Automation / Margin Pressure)
*   **Auto-Detailing:** AI drafting agents (e.g., EvolveLAB Glyph, SWAPP, Augmenta) generating 60–80% of standard details, schedules, and annotations.
*   **Drawing Set QA/QC:** Computer Vision models scanning CD sets for clashes, missing tags, dimension conflicts, and standard of care violations *before* issuance.
*   **Financial Impact:** **CD phase fee realization rates will drop 15–25%.** Fixed-fee contracts become dangerous; Time & Materials or Value-Based pricing required.

#### Phase 4: Construction Administration & Operations (Emerging Opportunity)
*   **Site Monitoring:** Drone/360-cam feeds + CV comparing As-Built vs. BIM in real-time (OpenSpace, Buildots, Disperse).
*   **RFI Automation:** LLMs parsing contracts/specs to draft RFI responses instantly.
*   **Digital Twin Handover:** AI-structured COBie data handover for Facilities Management – a **new recurring revenue stream** (Asset Information Management).

